<br>
My idea it to add some sort of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.utexas.edu/research/cem/publications/PDF/PR246.pdf" target="top">Rail Gun</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> to the system. What I see is it being used for mass rapid transit from the tornado/nuclear explosion zone to someplace of safety. <br>
<br>
As I am sure you are aware, tornadoes are often accompanied by violent electrical storms, and nuclear explosions produce massive electromagentic pulses. By harnessing these energies, it would possible to provide the magnetic power required to operate a large caliber rail gun. In order to make the deployment of this system feasible, reducing weight and size of the components is paramount, and so I plan on utilising the latest in nanotechnology.<br>
<br>
I would like to perform some experiments on the local fauna (squirrels, cast, then dogs and finally gnomes) to determine if the acceleration is adequate to propel those requiring rapid transit from the affected area. Initial calculations indicate this is feasible, but some consideration will also have to given to the g forces and other effects of accelerating from rest to 2km/sec in approximately 10msec. <br>
<br>
I would propose calling this part of the overall Tornado/Nuclear Device system: Fundin's Rail Gun Nanotechnical Homemade Rapid Transit System - which can be referred to as FRGN HRTS for short.<br>
<br>
